Luca Cari, spokesman for the fire rescue teams at the scene, confirmed the seven dead, saying rescue crews recovered several of the bodies from an area near the tower's submerged elevator.

There were fears that those still missing might be trapped inside the elevator, Cari said. There were no reports of missing ship crew.

'This event is unbelievable because 
we had the best weather navigation conditions,' said Luigi Merlo, 
president of the Genoa port authority. He declined to speculate on a 
cause, saying the ship had plenty of room to maneuver in the harbor and 
shouldn't have ended up so close to the dock.

