The five bodies recovered included 
three coast guard officials in the tower at the time of the crash, a 
port captain and a tugboat operator, said Cmdr. Filippo Marini, a coast 
guard spokesman. The bodies of the other two dead were being recovered, 
he said.

In a statement, Messina said it was 
fully cooperating with authorities to determine the cause of the 
'tragic' accident, which it said occurred during a normal maneuver to 
leave the port. It said Messina Line ships do the maneuver with 
regularity and are always accompanied by tugboats.

'There aren't words to express the 
dismay and profound condolences for the victims of this tragedy and 
their families,' Messina said in a statement.

